25|$|In India, the Labour Ministry formulates {{national}} {{policies on}} {{occupational safety and}} health in factories and docks with advice and assistance from Directorate General of Factory Advice Service and <b>Labour</b> <b>Institutes</b> (DGFASLI), and enforces its Policies through inspectorates of factories and inspectorates of dock safety. DGFASLI is the technical arm of the Ministry of Labour & Employment, Government of India and advises the factories on various problems concerning safety, health, efficiency and well - being of the persons at work places. The DGFASLI provides technical support in formulating rules, conducting occupational safety surveys and also for conducting occupational safety training programs.|$|R
